  1. Check missing values
miss.value = function(x){sum(is.na(x)/length(x))}
DT.miss = apply(X=DT, MARGIN = 2, FUN = miss.value)
round(DT.miss, 2)
sort(sapply(DT, function(x) { sum(is.na(x)) }), decreasing=TRUE)

#Income, ReferralProgram, Referred, PrimaryBank, ResolutionTimes, OnlineBanking, Service, NPS have missing values.
  1. Impute the missing values with mean
DT2$Income[is.na(DT2$Income)] = mean(DT2$Income, na.rm = TRUE)
round(DT2$Income,2)

DT2$Referred[is.na(DT2$Referred)] = mean(DT2$Referred, na.rm = TRUE)
round(DT2$Referred,2)

DT2$PrimaryBank[is.na(DT2$PrimaryBank)] = mean(DT2$PrimaryBank, na.rm = TRUE)
round(DT2$PrimaryBank,2)

DT2$ResolutionTimes[is.na(DT2$ResolutionTimes)] = mean(DT2$ResolutionTimes, na.rm = TRUE)
round(DT2$ResolutionTimes,2)

DT2$OnlineBanking[is.na(DT2$OnlineBanking)] = mean(DT2$OnlineBanking, na.rm = TRUE)
round(DT2$OnlineBanking,2)

DT2$Service[is.na(DT2$Service)] = mean(DT2$Service, na.rm = TRUE)
round(DT2$Service,2)

DT2$NPS[is.na(DT2$NPS)] = mean(DT2$NPS, na.rm = TRUE)
round(DT2$NPS,2)

  1. Correlation Plot

Need to reorder correlation plot

reorder_cor = function(cor){
dd = as.dist((1-cor)/2)
hc = hclust(dd)
cor = cor[hc$order, hc$order]
}
cor =  reorder_cor(cor)
upper_tri <- get_upper_tri(cor)
melted_cor <- melt(upper_tri, na.rm = TRUE)
ggheatmap <- ggplot(melted_cor, aes(Var2, Var1, fill = value))+
 geom_tile(color = "white")+
 scale_fill_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", 
   midpoint = 0, limit = c(-1,1), space = "Lab", 
    name="Pearson's Correlation") +
  theme_minimal()+ # minimal theme
 theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, 
    size = 12, hjust = 1))+
 coord_fixed()

ggheatmap + 
geom_text(aes(Var2, Var1, label = value), color = "black", size = 4) +
theme(
  axis.title.x = element_blank(),
  axis.title.y = element_blank(),

  panel.border = element_blank(),
  panel.background = element_blank(),

  1. Word cloud of NPS rating reason Load packges
library("tm")
library("SnowballC")
library("wordcloud")
library("RColorBrewer")

Load the column [Why] as corpus

why = DT2$Why
is.vector(why)
## [1] FALSE
words = Corpus(VectorSource(why))

Inspect the contents of column why

inspect(words)

Cleaning the text:

  1. clean up the special characters from the text.
toSpace = content_transformer(function(x,pattern) gsub(pattern," ", x))
words  = tm_map(words, toSpace, "/")
words  = tm_map(words, toSpace, "@")
words  = tm_map(words, toSpace, "NULL")
  1. Remove numbers, english common stopwords, punctuations, extra white spaces
words = tm_map(words,removeNumbers)
words = tm_map(words, removeWords, stopwords("english"))
words = tm_map(words, removePunctuation)
words = tm_map(words, stripWhitespace)
words = tm_map(words, removeWords, c("although","back","anyone","ago","around", "full", "will", "getting", "thing", "sometimes", "person", "made", "think", "keep", "overall", "etc", "minimum","customers", "really", "now","used","its","when","need", "still","business","bank","banks","always","also","one","can","get","account","atm","internet","website","the"))
  1. Build term-document matrix
dtm = TermDocumentMatrix(words)
m = as.matrix(dtm)
v = sort(rowSums(m),decreasing = TRUE)
d = data.frame(word = names(v), freq=v)
class(d)
#head(d,10)

  1. Find frequent terms

  2. Generate the word cloud

set.seed(10)

wordcloud(words = d$word, freq = d$freq, min.freq = 8, max.words = 100, random.order = FALSE, rot.per = 0.35, colors = brewer.pal(n=8, "Dark2"))
